He words it very scientifically and keeps talking about Tannin, which is extracted at high temperatures of coffee brewing, but I'm pretty sure they had equated it with caffeine at that time? But the ideal method he suggests of slowly pouring water is the Dr. Peat recommendation.

Someone said rose bushes have their thorns facing inwards, because they are trying to trap animals, who will starve, bleed, and rot into their roots, to nurture the plant. It is worthwhile to remember that both thorns and predation are results of the Fall. They mirror each other.

Mortality was a necessarily condition to impose after the Fall because it is the only state in which one can repent. Adam's work was actually to expand Eden, which is what we do after Liturgy going into the world. New Jerusalem won't be just a restoration, but the work continues.

Lord of Spirits podcast corrects so many delusions we hold. Adam didn't sin, Adam merely transgressed and "sin" entered the world through this. Cain committed the first sin. Christ's incarnation was going to take place even if the Fall didn't occur.

A young man is almost always young, but a baby is not merely young, but also something primordial, ancient, barbaric, very old, closer to a Mesopotamian idol than to a modern college student. Babies speak in old tongues. It is the infant that is God and the father that is his son

All language is Origami, because words have very sensible limitations and twisting through them to manage to betray some semblance of true meaning through things like structural composition of sentences, "shape" of text, context, form, etc. is the only way to say something real.

Dante off the top of my mind says something similar about The Virgin, being "her Son's daughter", but an echo of this applies to all patero-maternity. Every father meets an equal in his son's face, even a superior. Dr. Ray Peat already proved the biological superiority of babies.

People talk about every man having an inner child, but the truth is opposite: the house of the baby contains the house of man inside it, as every superior rank in a hierarchy contains all lower ranks within itself. A baby has "an inner man" and much more. Submit to your superior.
